# Frontend Definition of Done

A frontend task is done only when all apply:

## Functional + UX

- Behavior matches request and existing route/auth intent
- Loading/empty/error/success states are implemented where relevant
- UI is responsive at 320px, 768px, 1024px

## Accessibility + i18n

- Keyboard navigation works for all primary interactions
- ARIA labels/roles are present where semantic HTML is insufficient
- Focus-visible is clear and contrast meets WCAG AA intent
- New user-facing strings are i18n-ready

## Engineering Quality

- `bun run type-check` passes
- `bun run lint` passes
- `bun run build` passes
- `bun run test:run` passes
- `bun run test:e2e` passes for UI/route changes (or blocker is explicitly documented)

## Maintainability

- Reusable abstractions preferred over duplication
- No dead code introduced
- Docs/routes references stay consistent when changed
